713615f-b.title: Manhattan: 52nd Street - Broadway
713615f-b.text:
(1)

Broadway. In the foreground is the excavation on the site
of the old Hotel Albany, where the Hollywood Theatre will be
erected.
October 29, 1928.
P. L. Sperr.
(2 and 3)
A detail of same as viewed in an eastward direction and showing the
Guild Theatre at No. 245 West. This set consists of a negative and a
positive.
